# Cursor Rules for Portfolio Site Deployment

## 🚀 Deployment Workflow

### Automatic Deployment (Recommended)
- **GitHub Actions**: Automatically deploys to GitHub Pages when pushing to main branch
- **Trigger**: Any push to main branch
- **Result**: Site updated at https://muahuavang.github.io/My-Portfolio-Site/

### Manual Deployment
- **PowerShell**: Use `deploy.ps1` for Windows
- **Bash**: Use `deploy.sh` for cross-platform (Git Bash, WSL)
- **Git Commands**: Standard git workflow

## 📋 Pre-Deployment Checklist

Before deploying, ensure:
- [ ] All changes are tested locally
- [ ] No console errors in browser
- [ ] Responsive design works on mobile/tablet
- [ ] All links are functional
- [ ] Images are optimized
- [ ] Content is up-to-date

## 🔧 Quick Deploy Commands

### From Cursor Terminal (PowerShell)
```powershell
# Quick deploy with default message
.\deploy.ps1

# Deploy with custom commit message
.\deploy.ps1 -CommitMessage "Add new project section"

# Force deploy from any branch
.\deploy.ps1 -Force
```

### From Cursor Terminal (Git Bash)
```bash
# Quick deploy with default message
./deploy.sh

# Deploy with custom commit message
./deploy.sh -m "Add new project section"

# Force deploy from any branch
./deploy.sh -f
```

### Standard Git Commands
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Your commit message"
git push origin main
```

## 🎯 File Organization Rules

### HTML Structure
- Keep semantic HTML structure
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
- Include alt text for all images
- Maintain accessibility standards

### CSS Guidelines
- Use CSS variables for consistent theming
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Keep animations smooth (60fps)
- Use modern CSS features with fallbacks

### JavaScript Best Practices
- Minimize DOM manipulation
- Use event delegation where possible
- Implement proper error handling
- Keep functions small and focused

## 🚨 Common Issues & Solutions

### GitHub Pages Not Updating
1. Check GitHub Actions tab for deployment status
2. Verify gh-pages branch exists
3. Ensure GitHub Pages is enabled in repository settings
4. Wait 5-10 minutes for changes to propagate

### Build Errors
1. Check browser console for JavaScript errors
2. Validate HTML structure
3. Verify CSS syntax
4. Test in multiple browsers

### Performance Issues
1. Optimize images (compress, use WebP format)
2. Minimize CSS/JS files
3. Enable browser caching
4. Use CDN for external resources

